Package: MetaboPeak
Type: Package
Title: Functions to Work With Peaks from Metabolic Data Sets.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Renata Divinova
Maintainer: The package maintainer <divinova.r@czechglobe.cz>
Description: This library helps with the exploratory analysis of peaks from metabolic data sets. There are functions, that looks for the most abundant sample based on a m/z, calculate correlations between similar peaks in the same RT but different mass or plots the same peak in different time points based on the lowest variation. It is a usefull tool for checking data quality and gaining information about your data sets.    It is recomended to use this library with the manual look through chromatograms for the best results.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
